      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-rise validation against PIV benchmark data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted pressure rise across the centrifugal pump was compared against particle image velocimetry (PIV) benchmark measurements from the FDA pump study at five operating points. Agreement within 4.2% across all points. Uncertainty in experimental measurements characterised via Type A and Type B evaluation; structured UQ node captures both aleatory and epistemic contributions.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-pressure-rise-combined"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-velocity-field",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Velocity field comparison at pump impeller exit plane",
      "description": "Spatially resolved axial and tangential velocity profiles at the impeller exit plane were compared against LDV measurements from the FDA generic pump dataset. GCI-based discretization uncertainty was propagated through the comparison metric. Structured UQ node documents aleatory scatter in experimental repeat measurements.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-velocity-field-lda"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) validation across 5 flow-speed combinations",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values were converted to relative hemolysis index RH and compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements for the predicate pump across all five COU operating points. All five predictions satisfy RH < 1. Inherent variability in donor blood samples and assay repeatability was assessed qualitatively by the experimental team and noted in the test report; no structured uncertainty quantification node was linked to this result because the biological scatter was judged to fall within acceptable bounds without formal probabilistic characterisation."
    }
  ],
